{"hash":"gridsome","data":{"post":{"id":"154","title":"Git CheatSheet","summary":null,"body":"\n<h2>\n      <a id=\"article-force-pull\" class=\"anchor-hover hash-link\" href=\"#force-pull\">\n      #</a> Force pull</h2>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell\"><div class=\"code-bar\">\n      <span class=\"mdi mdi-content-copy\"></span>\n      <span class=\"code-lang\">shell</span>\n      </div><pre><code>git fetch\nget reset --hard origin/master</code></pre></div>\n<h2>\n      <a id=\"article-assume-unchanged\" class=\"anchor-hover hash-link\" href=\"#assume-unchanged\">\n      #</a> Assume unchanged</h2>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell\"><div class=\"code-bar\">\n      <span class=\"mdi mdi-content-copy\"></span>\n      <span class=\"code-lang\">shell</span>\n      </div><pre><code>git update-index --assume-unchanged exam.ple</code></pre></div>\n<h2>\n      <a id=\"article-upgrade-git-for-windows\" class=\"anchor-hover hash-link\" href=\"#upgrade-git-for-windows\">\n      #</a> Upgrade git for windows</h2>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell\"><div class=\"code-bar\">\n      <span class=\"mdi mdi-content-copy\"></span>\n      <span class=\"code-lang\">shell</span>\n      </div><pre><code>git update-git-for-windows</code></pre></div>\n<h2>\n      <a id=\"article-delete-tag\" class=\"anchor-hover hash-link\" href=\"#delete-tag\">\n      #</a> Delete tag</h2>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell\"><div class=\"code-bar\">\n      <span class=\"mdi mdi-content-copy\"></span>\n      <span class=\"code-lang\">shell</span>\n      </div><pre><code>git tag -d tagname\ngit push --delete origin tagname</code></pre></div>\n<h2>\n      <a id=\"article-remove-submodule\" class=\"anchor-hover hash-link\" href=\"#remove-submodule\">\n      #</a> Remove submodule</h2>\n<p><em>From <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/1260982/8810271\">https://stackoverflow.com/a/1260982/8810271</a></em></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Delete the relevant section from the <code>.gitmodules</code> file.</li>\n<li>Stage the <code>.gitmodules</code> changes:<br>\n<code>git add .gitmodules</code></li>\n<li>Delete the relevant section from <code>.git/config</code>.</li>\n<li>Remove the submodule files from the working tree and index:<br>\n<code>git rm --cached path_to_submodule</code> (no trailing slash).</li>\n<li>Remove the submodule's <code>.git</code> directory:<br>\n<code>rm -rf .git/modules/path_to_submodule</code></li>\n<li>Commit the changes:<br>\n<code>git commit -m \"Removed submodule &lt;name&gt;\"</code></li>\n<li>Delete the now untracked submodule files:<br>\n<code>rm -rf path_to_submodule</code></li>\n</ol>","createdAt":"2020-12-09T07:32:18.000Z","lastEditedAt":"2021-01-21T00:50:30.000Z","image":null,"serializedHeadings":"[{\"level\":2,\"slug\":\"force-pull\",\"content\":\"Force pull\"},{\"level\":2,\"slug\":\"assume-unchanged\",\"content\":\"Assume unchanged\"},{\"level\":2,\"slug\":\"upgrade-git-for-windows\",\"content\":\"Upgrade git for windows\"},{\"level\":2,\"slug\":\"delete-tag\",\"content\":\"Delete tag\"},{\"level\":2,\"slug\":\"remove-submodule\",\"content\":\"Remove submodule\"}]","labels":[{"id":"blog: cheatsheet"}]}},"context":{}}